headline: Walmart, Amazon Shares Slump on Tariffs Plans
summary: Shares of big U.S. retailers sold off on Trump’s plan to add tariffs ranging from at least 10% to as much as 49% on imports depending on the country of origin. Walmart, Amazon, Best Buy and Target were lower following the initial announcement.
